1
00:00:55,088 --> 00:01:02,600
"180 Degree Longitude Passes Through Us"

2
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:05,000
(Previously)
My Dad named me Wang.

3
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,777
Sasiwimol is my mom.

4
00:01:06,777 --> 00:01:10,755
It’s time to take my handsome prince to the north.

5
00:01:10,755 --> 00:01:12,755
You’ve done enough already. I’m driving.

6
00:01:12,755 --> 00:01:14,755
My gosh, stop it.

7
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:16,777
You stay in the car. I’ll be back.

8
00:01:16,777 --> 00:01:17,511
Wang.

9
00:01:17,755 --> 00:01:20,355
I'm sorry but my car has gotten stuck.
It's about 200 meters from the entrance..

10
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:21,822
Sangkam, get the equipment.

11
00:01:22,422 --> 00:01:24,933
- In? Inthawut?
- Mol.

12
00:01:26,288 --> 00:01:27,155
It’s unbelievable.

13
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:32,222
My long-lost nephew of all people
got lost and wandered to my place.

14
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,333
When you turned down Ornjira, the beauty of the campus,

15
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:40,577
she completely stopped going for men.

16
00:01:40,777 --> 00:01:46,440
In the end, she got together
with that fourth year girl, Nuansamorn.

17
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:50,422
I’m telling you those engineering
students were enraged.

18
00:01:51,288 --> 00:01:53,933
What’s the main course?
It smells so good.

19
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:56,444
Fried chicken with ma kwaen.
What do you think, Wang?

20
00:01:56,577 --> 00:01:57,466
It’s really good.

21
00:01:58,133 --> 00:02:01,022
Actually, it wasn’t just Ornjira
who got her heart broken.

22
00:02:01,155 --> 00:02:03,444
You turned down a lot of girls.

23
00:02:03,577 --> 00:02:07,511
At the time,
everyone was so crazy about you.

24
00:02:07,511 --> 00:02:08,911
Inthawut, the architecture student.

25
00:02:09,511 --> 00:02:11,311
Whenever you came
for our rehearsals,

26
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:17,060
your fans would always be there to greet you
with plenty of treats for you to try.

27
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:19,888
Why did he turn them down?
Was there a special girl that he was into?

28
00:02:19,955 --> 00:02:24,688
No, there wasn’t.
He just wasn’t interested in any girls.

29
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,377
Mol, more wine?

30
00:02:29,888 --> 00:02:32,333
And how did you get him to do your play?

31
00:02:32,688 --> 00:02:38,511
I had plenty of tricks
back in the day, you know?

32
00:02:38,777 --> 00:02:45,844
I went to his rugby match and wouldn’t
leave him alone until he said yes.

33
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,977
But I couldn’t act to save my life.

34
00:02:48,177 --> 00:02:49,555
Did you play rugby too?

35
00:02:49,555 --> 00:02:51,266
No, I was in the audience.

36
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,333
The drama majors were so jealous of me.

37
00:02:54,511 --> 00:02:59,955
Not only did I get him to join my play,
I also got to be with a rugby player.

38
00:03:01,577 --> 00:03:02,466
You mean Dad?

39
00:03:03,911 --> 00:03:05,733
Actually, your dad was the real hot shot.

40
00:03:06,155 --> 00:03:09,866
Your mom cast me in her play
only because she fell in love with him.

41
00:03:10,488 --> 00:03:13,177
I knew that if I had to get to him,
I'd have to befriend his best friend.

42
00:03:14,955 --> 00:03:15,955
Are you finished, Mol?

43
00:03:16,911 --> 00:03:19,200
Yes, normally I don’t even eat dinner.

44
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,400
That's because "normally" wine is your dinner.

45
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:23,733
People don’t call me the female Dionysus for nothing.

46
00:03:27,911 --> 00:03:29,155
You should eat some more.

47
00:03:30,111 --> 00:03:31,088
Thank you.

48
00:03:31,777 --> 00:03:34,422
How long did you study abroad?

49
00:03:35,088 --> 00:03:37,133
It was for my Master’s and a PhD, almost five years in total.

50
00:03:37,466 --> 00:03:40,133
Did you not have anyone while you were there?

51
00:03:40,911 --> 00:03:42,044
Anyone? Who?

52
00:03:42,044 --> 00:03:46,222
Zero point. You know who
I’m talking about. Your exes.

53
00:03:47,066 --> 00:03:50,666
How could I date? It was hard
enough to focus on my study.

54
00:03:50,888 --> 00:03:53,150
I was on a scholarship. I had to
graduate before the grant ran out.

55
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:54,666
Even after graduation?

56
00:03:54,844 --> 00:03:56,200
Are you doing an interview
for a magazine or what?

57
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:58,666
Zero point. You didn’t answer my question.

58
00:03:59,822 --> 00:04:03,622
Oh, my. He’s gotten you cornered.

59
00:04:05,088 --> 00:04:07,844
- Reminds me of a certain someone.
- Well?

60
00:04:09,422 --> 00:04:15,733
How should I put it? I’m a man.
It’d be weird if I wasn’t seeing anyone.

61
00:04:16,311 --> 00:04:18,666
But in the end you broke it off with everyone?

62
00:04:18,888 --> 00:04:23,088
Why are we discussing my love life?

63
00:04:24,466 --> 00:04:26,666
What about you Wang? Are you seeing anyone?

64
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:32,288
I’m a man. It’d be weird if I wasn't.

65
00:04:33,311 --> 00:04:35,133
How many points
should he get for this answer?

66
00:04:35,311 --> 00:04:37,933
I give him a ten out of ten.

67
00:04:41,622 --> 00:04:42,555
Are you done?

68
00:04:42,688 --> 00:04:45,955
I couldn’t eat no more. I’ve never
tried something like this in Bangkok.

69
00:04:46,688 --> 00:04:49,777
Sangkam would be happy to know
you loved his food.

70
00:04:50,155 --> 00:04:52,200
Do you want your dessert now?

71
00:04:52,844 --> 00:04:58,777
Thank you, but I prefer
to have my wine as dessert.

72
00:04:58,844 --> 00:05:00,111
What about the gentleman here?

73
00:05:01,155 --> 00:05:02,222
No, I don’t eat desserts.

74
00:05:02,977 --> 00:05:05,977
In that case, let’s relocate there.

75
00:05:06,488 --> 00:05:08,866
This lady here is dying to wash
all the food down with her wine.

76
00:05:09,355 --> 00:05:14,044
As for you, I’ll make you
another glass of warm milk.

77
00:05:16,466 --> 00:05:22,533
Hooray! Party! Party!

78
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:27,622
To the happy accident today
that brought us together.

79
00:05:32,177 --> 00:05:37,400
And… to my son who made it happen.

80
00:05:44,822 --> 00:05:47,488
I’m going to take a shower.
Is the water warm?

81
00:05:50,755 --> 00:05:54,200
You can use the shower in my bedroom.
The bathroom has an electric shower.

82
00:05:54,644 --> 00:05:55,888
Sure. I’ll do that.

83
00:05:56,311 --> 00:06:00,266
Someone's happened to mess up
the electric shower in her room already.

84
00:06:01,644 --> 00:06:02,688
If you’ll excuse me.

85
00:06:17,288 --> 00:06:20,466
Won’t you ask me for a dance?

86
00:08:05,288 --> 00:08:08,330
I’m glad I decided to stay with you tonight.

87
00:08:08,330 --> 00:08:11,177
Otherwise, who knows what would’ve happened to us?

88
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:17,044
This is normal up here.
You don’t know when it’s going to rain.

89
00:08:17,288 --> 00:08:20,333
But here you don’t have to
worry about it when it rains.

90
00:08:20,622 --> 00:08:26,466
Unlike in Bangkok, where rain
means traffic and flooding issues.

91
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:30,733
If you’re lucky, you’ll might as well even see a sea of fog

92
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:33,911
from your bedroom early in the morning.

93
00:08:34,822 --> 00:08:36,511
That is if I can wake up that early...

94
00:08:39,688 --> 00:08:43,177
Wang’s been gone for quite a while.
He said he was going for a shower?

95
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:45,288
Did he go to sleep?

96
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:48,977
I’ll go check on him, my lady.

97
00:08:49,377 --> 00:08:51,155
And come straight to me when you’re done.

98
00:08:51,288 --> 00:08:55,377
You don’t really want to
leave a lady alone with her wine.

99
00:08:56,555 --> 00:08:58,244
There’s a cave underneath this house.

100
00:08:58,511 --> 00:09:01,933
I'ver set up a cellar to store all of the wine.
There’s even a wine bath.

101
00:09:02,288 --> 00:09:05,177
You can drink all day
and the wine won’t run out.

102
00:09:06,955 --> 00:09:08,177
Are you for real?

103
00:09:08,288 --> 00:09:10,377
No, I was messing with you.

104
00:09:10,888 --> 00:09:11,866
Gosh.

105
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:48,200
I’m sorry I didn’t bring my towel,
so I used the one you had in the bathroom.

106
00:09:48,422 --> 00:09:49,666
You don't mind, right?

107
00:09:56,777 --> 00:09:58,177
Here. Use the clean one.

108
00:10:19,466 --> 00:10:20,311
Thank you.

109
00:10:29,244 --> 00:10:32,311
Your mom asked me to check up on you.
She’s having the time of her life.

110
00:10:32,511 --> 00:10:34,622
Go up to her when you’re done.

111
00:10:42,177 --> 00:10:44,088
I think we have a lot in common.

112
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:51,022
I guess you’ve been to
several destinations around the world?

113
00:10:55,111 --> 00:10:56,333
No, I’ve only been to some.

114
00:10:58,622 --> 00:11:00,533
There are places I've never been to.

115
00:11:02,733 --> 00:11:04,088
And there are places I simply don’t want to visit.

116
00:11:06,377 --> 00:11:07,311
How come?

117
00:11:09,533 --> 00:11:14,022
You don’t like travelling to new places?

118
00:11:17,777 --> 00:11:18,688
No.

119
00:11:21,622 --> 00:11:24,066
So you're someone who prefers
his comfort zone?

120
00:11:26,711 --> 00:11:27,755
I guess that's the case.

121
00:11:35,911 --> 00:11:39,977
So, in a way, you’re rather old-fashioned.

122
00:11:42,044 --> 00:11:45,888
I listen to and most of the time
side with the younger generation,

123
00:11:48,177 --> 00:11:49,444
but sometimes it’s…

124
00:11:49,711 --> 00:11:51,355
You don’t want to go out of your way?

125
00:11:59,244 --> 00:12:02,777
You should go. Mom doesn’t like to be kept waiting.

126
00:12:03,711 --> 00:12:04,911
I’ll join you in a while.

127
00:12:11,888 --> 00:12:15,622
Wait. Can I sleep in your room tonight?

128
00:12:16,844 --> 00:12:17,844
I swear I don’t snore.

129
00:12:21,177 --> 00:12:23,333
Sure. You can sleep wherever you want.

130
00:12:42,622 --> 00:12:44,622
Looks like it won’t
stop raining anytime soon.

131
00:12:45,733 --> 00:12:50,288
So what? Is there a problem?

132
00:12:50,844 --> 00:12:53,488
We’re building a bridge over there.

133
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:57,422
To help make it easier for
the villagers to go to the main road.

134
00:12:57,955 --> 00:13:00,800
If it continues to rain,
we have have to halt everything.

135
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:05,044
That means those villagers
get to walk freely around your house?

136
00:13:05,288 --> 00:13:06,044
Yes.

137
00:13:06,511 --> 00:13:11,440
Are you sure they can be trusted?
You’ll get yourself killed one day.

138
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:14,488
The people here can be trusted.
They’re not dangerous.

139
00:13:14,622 --> 00:13:15,866
How can you be so sure?

140
00:13:15,933 --> 00:13:18,844
I thought you went to several volunteer
camps in the countryside when you were in college.

141
00:13:19,511 --> 00:13:21,333
And yet you look down on villagers?

142
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,822
Are you done with your bath, my prince?

143
00:13:24,977 --> 00:13:27,844
Would you do me a favour
and dance with me?

144
00:13:27,955 --> 00:13:31,533
Oh, my. You barely set foot here
and the lights are out.

145
00:13:31,750 --> 00:13:36,088
It’s to be expected.
Especially when it rains.

146
00:13:36,088 --> 00:13:37,533
That’s why we have candles around.

147
00:13:40,911 --> 00:13:42,377
I’ll help. I have a lighter.

148
00:13:42,622 --> 00:13:44,933
Why are you carrying a lighter, Wang?

149
00:13:45,244 --> 00:13:46,777
To burn paper, I guess.

150
00:13:47,822 --> 00:13:49,444
Watch your mouth, kiddo.

151
00:14:12,822 --> 00:14:16,022
- Any more candles, In?
- No, thanks.

152
00:14:21,444 --> 00:14:25,822
My gosh. This is romantic.

153
00:14:26,711 --> 00:14:29,133
The power could be out
all night unless it stops raining.

154
00:14:30,888 --> 00:14:32,511
I love it, though.

155
00:14:32,511 --> 00:14:36,311
It’s dark.
Everything’s prettier this way.

156
00:14:36,488 --> 00:14:38,577
Like in TV dramas.

157
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:42,044
I have an idea.

158
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:45,288
We should do a play
and take a trip down memory lane.

159
00:14:45,288 --> 00:14:47,466
We can’t exactly listen to music now.

160
00:14:47,466 --> 00:14:49,466
Do you still remember your lines?

161
00:14:49,866 --> 00:14:51,577
From Julie, My Lady?

162
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:54,933
I’ll be Julie tonight.

163
00:14:55,088 --> 00:14:58,488
Julie comes down to the kitchen

164
00:14:58,666 --> 00:15:02,133
to find her handsome servant

165
00:15:02,488 --> 00:15:06,355
with a young maid
who’s sitting with her head down,

166
00:15:06,355 --> 00:15:08,355
tired from her kitchen duties.

167
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,155
Wang, go sit over there.

168
00:15:13,422 --> 00:15:18,577
Seeing them together makes Julie
want to win him over even more.

169
00:15:19,577 --> 00:15:21,866
Can I sleep for real?
I don’t want to see this.

170
00:15:22,222 --> 00:15:25,422
Pour me more wine, Jean.

171
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:31,866
But I thought in the play, Julie liked beer?

172
00:15:33,177 --> 00:15:37,777
Today is different. She wants wine.

173
00:15:41,844 --> 00:15:43,555
And go do your bow.

174
00:15:46,711 --> 00:15:54,200
Now, kneel before me and kiss my foot.

175
00:15:54,688 --> 00:15:57,244
So this was your favourite genre
of play even back in college?

176
00:15:57,533 --> 00:16:00,111
What do you know?

177
00:16:00,355 --> 00:16:07,200
Every girl dreams to have a handsome,
young man kneel before her.

178
00:16:07,511 --> 00:16:10,155
And to have her foot kissed?
What for?

179
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:13,333
It’s to show him she owns him.

180
00:16:13,777 --> 00:16:19,444
The handsome servant betrayed her
by getting chummy with that young maid.

181
00:16:19,755 --> 00:16:21,000
What a terrible character.

182
00:16:21,466 --> 00:16:24,244
Well it’s not like she’s real.

183
00:16:25,155 --> 00:16:29,000
My son takes this very seriously.

184
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:33,822
He values human dignity
and despises class systems.

185
00:16:34,177 --> 00:16:37,755
He can’t stand injustice even in movies.

186
00:16:41,177 --> 00:16:45,511
You should know we make movies and
TV shows to escape reality.

187
00:16:45,866 --> 00:16:49,577
Because life’s already hard enough.

188
00:16:51,177 --> 00:16:52,311
Are you drunk?

189
00:16:53,155 --> 00:16:55,422
No, just a bit tipsy.

190
00:16:56,777 --> 00:17:03,444
You know? In told me there is
a cave with a wine cellar underneath the house.

191
00:17:03,711 --> 00:17:09,888
There’s even a wine bath.
I want to get into that bath for once.

192
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:11,977
You believe that story?

193
00:17:12,222 --> 00:17:15,955
I prefer to live in my imagination.

194
00:17:16,311 --> 00:17:19,444
Especially when the truth isn’t pretty.

195
00:17:20,066 --> 00:17:21,355
You’re wise when you’re drunk.

196
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:23,755
As expected from the big and successful director.

197
00:17:24,844 --> 00:17:28,955
Now tell me, In. Have you seen any of my shows?

198
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,555
Don’t get mad.

199
00:17:32,711 --> 00:17:33,466
But no.

200
00:17:36,377 --> 00:17:42,600
Too bad. You know
all my shows were a success.

201
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:45,644
Everyone loves them.

202
00:17:46,088 --> 00:17:48,488
Actually, I don’t even watch TV.

203
00:17:48,555 --> 00:17:49,711
Look around you.

204
00:17:49,955 --> 00:17:52,777
There is no TV here
except in the guest room.

205
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,111
I don't even have a Wi-Fi connection.

206
00:17:56,533 --> 00:18:02,800
Inthawut, you truly are a real introvert.

207
00:18:03,155 --> 00:18:07,733
How am I going to contact the outside world then?

208
00:18:07,844 --> 00:18:09,422
There’s a landline over here.

209
00:18:10,177 --> 00:18:12,666
Classic.

210
00:18:16,222 --> 00:18:19,777
But how do we use it? Let me try.

211
00:18:19,911 --> 00:18:22,155
911.

212
00:18:23,133 --> 00:18:24,400
Hello.

213
00:18:25,155 --> 00:18:30,800
Please, help me. I’ve been taken
against my will to an ancient cave.

214
00:18:31,422 --> 00:18:35,444
I can’t find my way out.
I’m not even sure if there’s a way out.

215
00:18:35,711 --> 00:18:38,955
What are you talking about?
You got lost and ended up here.

216
00:18:39,822 --> 00:18:43,800
Yes, I always get lost when I drive.

217
00:18:44,066 --> 00:18:50,888
But it wasn’t my fault this time.
It was his. He brought us here.

218
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:56,711
Tell me about your job.
What kind of lakorn (Thai soap operas) do you make?

219
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,222
I bet it’s progressive.

220
00:18:58,444 --> 00:19:03,377
On the contrary,
she’s a bit of a hypocrite.

221
00:19:03,711 --> 00:19:07,222
She looks flashy on the outside,
but everything she does is a remake.

222
00:19:08,333 --> 00:19:10,844
Well, I think of my creation as a fine wine.

223
00:19:11,155 --> 00:19:13,955
The older the wine, the better it tastes.

224
00:19:15,022 --> 00:19:17,200
And you came here for what sort of a project?

225
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,288
It’s called Engraved in Your Heart.

226
00:19:20,377 --> 00:19:22,955
- Sounds familiar.
- Right?

227
00:19:23,288 --> 00:19:28,577
The title only has to be familiar for it to work.

228
00:19:28,577 --> 00:19:33,000
It doesn’t matter if it’s a remake as long as we restyle it.

229
00:19:33,577 --> 00:19:34,711
So what’s the story about?

230
00:19:35,688 --> 00:19:38,888
A young maiden falling in love with a much older man.

231
00:19:39,377 --> 00:19:41,177
Daddy issues.

232
00:19:41,622 --> 00:19:45,977
The theme is rather common in English literature.

233
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:53,444
But since it’s a lakorn, the male lead has to be a prince.

234
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:56,888
I added jealousy and everything for a little spice.

235
00:19:57,177 --> 00:19:59,733
In the end, the maiden gets everything.

236
00:19:59,955 --> 00:20:01,977
Everyone is happy.

237
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:05,000
The viewers want this because
they want to have that kind of romance.

238
00:20:05,222 --> 00:20:07,644
That's why they call it romance.

239
00:20:08,088 --> 00:20:13,311
But unlike the previous versions,
my prince comes from the north.

240
00:20:13,977 --> 00:20:15,000
That’s all?

241
00:20:16,022 --> 00:20:19,755
- He doesn’t like what I do.
- It’s not that I don’t like what you do.

242
00:20:19,930 --> 00:20:22,222
- It’s not progressive enough.
- I just don’t like lakorns because

