For reminding me what I should do.

497
00:41:29,466 --> 00:41:31,933
See you tomorrow. Goodnight.

498
00:41:34,577 --> 00:41:35,600
Goodnight.

499
00:42:14,244 --> 00:42:17,844
That was the first time I wanted
someone to put a blanket on me.

500
00:42:20,466 --> 00:42:22,777
I feel the blanket is warmer this way.

501
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:31,066
That night, despite no one putting a blanket on me,

502
00:42:33,311 --> 00:42:36,755
somehow I felt warmth and slept like a baby.

503
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:42,355
I dove and dove into a void that we call a dream.

504
00:42:44,933 --> 00:42:47,666
Eventually, I arrived at the heart of it.

505
00:42:56,444 --> 00:42:59,444
In the dream, his back was turned to me,

506
00:43:01,111 --> 00:43:03,088
but I knew it was Dad.

507
00:43:06,088 --> 00:43:08,733
It’s weird because I just had this big fight with Mom.

508
00:43:10,444 --> 00:43:12,666
And yet, she wasn’t there in the dream.

509
00:43:16,733 --> 00:43:18,000
The one who appeared

510
00:43:22,555 --> 00:43:23,533
turned out to be In.

511
00:43:33,511 --> 00:43:36,866
I saw Dad and In,
walking out of the game together.

512
00:43:37,777 --> 00:43:39,977
I ran after them. I shouted to my dad.

513
00:43:40,244 --> 00:43:43,530
It'd been so long. I missed my dad.

514
00:43:43,530 --> 00:43:45,000
But he didn’t seem to hear me.

515
00:43:45,466 --> 00:43:47,288
I mustered all my strength

516
00:43:47,422 --> 00:43:49,933
and charged at them, as if I was
a rugby player scoring a touchdown.

517
00:43:50,888 --> 00:43:53,933
Finally, the two stopped walking.

518
00:43:54,644 --> 00:43:56,111
In turned around and smiled at me.

519
00:43:56,777 --> 00:43:58,666
And Dad took off his cap.

520
00:44:00,222 --> 00:44:01,466
But it wasn’t Dad that I saw.

521
00:44:02,422 --> 00:44:03,955
It was me.

522
00:45:29,377 --> 00:45:31,177
(Next Episode)
Don’t forget about your promise from last night.

523
00:45:31,355 --> 00:45:32,133
What promise?

524
00:45:32,200 --> 00:45:33,777
To apologise to your mom.

525
00:45:33,866 --> 00:45:36,150
I don’t know if I should
continue making lakorns.

526
00:45:36,150 --> 00:45:38,444
No one appreciates them.

527
00:45:39,088 --> 00:45:41,444
What I do means nothing to you?

528
00:45:41,688 --> 00:45:44,644
I think I should go ahead
and get the bridge done by myself.

529
00:45:44,755 --> 00:45:46,155
Do you want to help?

530
00:45:47,000 --> 00:45:47,822
Sure.

531
00:45:47,822 --> 00:45:50,377
Sangkam was right. It’s a simple bridge.

532
00:45:50,755 --> 00:45:52,155
There’s no need for complicated designs.

533
00:45:52,244 --> 00:45:54,711
Can you handle saws and nails?

534
00:45:54,822 --> 00:45:55,977
You can teach me how to.
